cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is about a new multi-attention learning model for image segmentation, which is a common task in computer vision (CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a new mechanism for adjusting the loss weight of each pixel prediction separately, which is related to machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) techniques. Therefore, the second most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language), which are also related to ML and DL. Finally, the paper uses gland segmentation as a showcase application, which is a medical image analysis task, and may be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
